ation time\ninitially and saturates when the diffusion distance is much larger than the\nsize of the inhomogeneity or $t^3\\gg 3\\omega^2\\sigma^2/\\hat q_0$. The\ntransverse momentum broadening due to the inhomogeneity also saturates at late\ntime in contrast to the continued increase with time if the drifted diffusion\nin space is ignored.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Apr 2022 18:00:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-12"}
