s and elements' embeddings.\nFinally, we develop a set-batch algorithm to improve the model efficiency,\nwhich can create time-consistent batches in advance and achieve 3.5x training\nspeedups on average. Experiments on real-world datasets demonstrate the\neffectiveness and good interpretability of our approach.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Apr 2022 02:49:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 13 Apr 2022 03:06:27 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 14 Apr 2022 09:53:13 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 17 Jun 2022 13:03:46 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Wed, 13 Jul 2022 05:49:40 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Sun, 31 Jul 2022 05:06:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-02"}
